#: src/rust-next/no-more-fnbox.md:5
msgid "The book used to have this code in Chapter 20, section 2:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/no-more-fnbox.md:21
msgid ""
"Here, we define a new trait called `FnBox`, and then implement it for all "
"`FnOnce` closures. All the implementation does is call the closure. These "
"sorts of hacks were needed because a `Box<dyn FnOnce>` didn't implement "
"`FnOnce`. This was true for all three posibilities:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/no-more-fnbox.md:26
msgid "`Box<dyn Fn>` and `Fn`"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/no-more-fnbox.md:27
msgid "`Box<dyn FnMut>` and `FnMut`"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/no-more-fnbox.md:28
msgid "`Box<dyn FnOnce>` and `FnOnce`"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/no-more-fnbox.md:30
msgid ""
"However, as of Rust 1.35, these traits are implemented for these types, and "
"so the `FnBox` trick is no longer required. In the latest version of the "
"book, the `Job` type looks like this:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/no-more-fnbox.md:38
msgid "No need for all that other code."
msgstr ""
